sec.p:
Motivated by the statistical test used in the biomarker‐driven design proposed by Jiang et al. (2007) [18], we consider a generalized model as described in Section 3 but where the biomarker is considered as a binary variable. In detail, the following procedure is considered:
the biomarker space is divided into a set of values {c1,c2,…,cI};
for each value, ci with i∈{1,…,I}, a linear logistic model is fitted as following Y(k)∼Tk+1X>ci+Tk×1X>ci, where 1 is the indicator function. The p‐value, pci, for the interaction term (Tk×1X>ci) is computed;
the minimum p‐value pmin=minci∈{c1,c2,…cI}pci for the interaction term is selected and compared to the pre‐specified αITD level chosen to control the type I error rate at α.
